This paper focuses on user participation and behavior on a social news aggregator, which falls under the categories of social media and human-computer interaction. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper analyzes user data and activity, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of a controversy on user participation, which could relate to cybersecurity and online communities, falling under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
